> Would one of you be willing to contribute a fix for the Gradle plugin?

@gsmet I just opened a PR for this. It simply removes the dependency on the `test` task, because that is why the tests are running unexpectedly.

Arguably, the `quarkusIntTest` _should_ have a dependency on the Gradle lifecycle task `check`, so that Gradle users may run both the `test` and `quarkusIntTest` tasks by simply executing `check`. I did not make this change, but am I happy to include it.
